{
  "text": "We use the comprehensive index (Inverted Generational Distance, IGD) [CITATION_1] to evaluate the proposed algorithm. The test environment is: Windows10, CPU is Intel Xeon-E3-1240v5, 3.5GHZ, and 8G. The test software is MATLAB 2014A. IGD is a metric to measure the distance between the real Pareto frontier and the approximate Pareto frontiers obtained by the algorithm. The lower the IGD value, the better the convergence and diversity of the approximate Pareto fronts obtained by the algorithm, and the closer to the real Pareto frontiers. The calculation formula is as follows:",
